VALUES
(42, 11, 49, 20, 1, 2, 6, 'wisdom of God', 'Wisdom and Prophetic Instruction', 'Both passages emphasize the role of wisdom in guiding and instructing people. Luke mentions the sending of prophets, while Proverbs speaks of understanding and instruction, highlighting the importance of wisdom in both contexts.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 49, 46, 1, 24, 24, 'wisdom of God', 'Connection of Wisdom in God', 'This connection highlights the theme of wisdom ascribed to God in both passages. In Luke, the wisdom of God sends prophets, while in Corinthians, Christ is described as the wisdom of God.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 49, 49, 4, 11, 11, 'prophets and apostles', 'Connection of Apostles and Prophets', 'This connection highlights the roles of apostles and prophets in both passages. Luke 11:49 mentions sending prophets and apostles, while Ephesians 4:11 lists them as gifts to the church.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 49, 20, 9, 1, 3, 'wisdom of God', 'Connection of Wisdom and Prophets', 'This connection highlights the role of wisdom in sending forth messengers, as seen in both passages. Proverbs describes wisdom''s active role in calling out, while Luke references wisdom''s intention to send prophets and apostles.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 49, 40, 22, 6, 6, 'they shall slay and persecute', 'Connection of Prophets and Persecution', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of persecution against God''s messengers. Luke 11:49 mentions the sending of prophets and their persecution, while Matthew 22:6 describes the mistreatment and killing of servants sent by the master.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 50, 1, 9, 5, 6, 'the blood of all the prophets', 'Connection of Blood Requirement', 'This connection highlights the theme of blood being required for wrongdoing. Both passages emphasize the accountability for the shedding of blood, whether of prophets or of man.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 50, 66, 18, 20, 24, 'the blood of all the prophets', 'Connection of Bloodshed and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the blood of prophets, linking the judgment of a generation in Luke to the condemnation of Babylon in Revelation. This connection highlights the theme of divine retribution for the shedding of innocent blood.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 50, 4, 35, 33, 33, 'blood of all the prophets', 'Connection of Blood and Defilement', 'This connection highlights the theme of blood as a defilement of the land. Both passages emphasize the consequences of shedding blood, with Luke referencing the blood of prophets and Numbers discussing the pollution of land due to bloodshed.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 50, 12, 24, 4, 4, 'the blood of all the prophets', 'Connection of Innocent Blood', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of bloodshed, specifically the blood of prophets and the innocent blood in Jerusalem. This connection highlights the accountability for violence against the righteous.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 50, 19, 9, 12, 12, 'blood of all the prophets', 'Connection of Blood and Justice', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of blood and accountability. Luke 11:50 speaks of the blood of prophets being required, while Psalms 9:12 mentions making inquisition for blood, highlighting a divine remembrance of justice.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 50, 2, 20, 5, 5, 'the blood of all the prophets', 'Generational Consequences of Iniquity', 'This connection highlights the theme of iniquity affecting generations. Both passages emphasize the consequences of rejecting God and the bloodshed of prophets, linking the actions of one generation to the suffering of future generations.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 50, 23, 26, 21, 21, 'the blood of all the prophets', 'Connection of Blood and Iniquity', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of bloodshed and divine judgment. Luke 11:50 speaks of the blood of prophets required for iniquity, while Isaiah 26:21 mentions the earth disclosing blood due to iniquity.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 51, 14, 24, 20, 22, 'the blood of Zacharias', 'Connection of Violence Against Prophets', 'Both passages emphasize the violence against God''s messengers. Luke references the blood of Zacharias, who was stoned for speaking God''s truth, paralleling Abel''s unjust murder. This connection highlights the theme of accountability for such acts.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 51, 40, 23, 35, 35, 'from the blood of Abel', 'Connection of Righteous Blood', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of righteous bloodshed, linking Abel and Zacharias as examples of violence against the innocent. This connection highlights the continuity of judgment upon those responsible for such acts across generations.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 51, 58, 11, 4, 4, 'the blood of Abel', 'Connection Between Abel and Righteousness', 'This connection highlights the theme of righteous sacrifice, as both passages reference Abel''s blood and his righteous standing before God. Abel''s offering is contrasted with the violence against prophets, linking the idea of faith and sacrifice across generations.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 51, 62, 3, 12, 12, 'the blood of Abel', 'Connection of Cain and Abel', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of violence stemming from jealousy and evil actions. Luke references Abel''s blood, while 1 John contrasts Cain''s wickedness with Abel''s righteousness.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 51, 1, 4, 8, 11, 'blood of Abel', 'Connection of Bloodshed', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of bloodshed and its consequences. Luke references Abel''s blood, linking it to the broader context of violence against the righteous.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 51, 38, 1, 1, 1, 'blood of Abel', 'Connection of Martyrdom Themes', 'This connection highlights the theme of bloodshed, as both Abel and Zechariah represent victims of violence. The mention of ''blood'' in Luke 11:51 and the prophetic role of Zechariah in Zechariah 1:1 emphasize the continuity of martyrdom in biblical history.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 51, 58, 12, 24, 24, 'the blood of Abel', 'Connection of Abel''s Blood', 'This connection highlights the theme of bloodshed, linking Abel''s blood as a symbol of injustice to the blood of Jesus, which offers redemption. Both passages emphasize the significance of blood in the context of sacrifice and covenant.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 52, 40, 23, 13, 13, NULL, 'Woes to Religious Leaders', 'Both passages emphasize the failure of religious leaders to enter the kingdom and their role in hindering others. They highlight the consequences of their actions in relation to the ''kingdom of heaven'' and ''key of knowledge.''', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 52, 39, 2, 7, 7, 'key of knowledge', 'Knowledge and Leadership in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the importance of knowledge in spiritual leadership. Both passages emphasize the responsibility of leaders to provide and protect knowledge, with Luke condemning those who hinder access and Malachi affirming the priest''s role in keeping knowledge.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 52, 42, 11, 45, 46, 'key of knowledge', 'Burden of Knowledge and Law', 'Both passages emphasize the burdens imposed by lawyers on others while they themselves do not engage with the knowledge they claim to uphold. This connection highlights the hypocrisy of the lawyers in their roles as interpreters of the law.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 52, 44, 4, 17, 18, 'them that were entering in ye hindered', 'Obstruction of Knowledge', 'This connection highlights the theme of hindrance in the pursuit of knowledge. In Luke, the lawyers prevent others from entering into understanding, while in Acts, the authorities threaten the apostles to stop spreading their message.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 52, 43, 9, 24, 34, 'key of knowledge', 'Knowledge and Spiritual Blindness', 'This connection highlights the theme of knowledge and understanding in both passages. In Luke, the lawyers hinder others from entering into knowledge, while in John, the blind man confronts the religious leaders'' lack of understanding about Jesus'' divine authority.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 52, 43, 7, 47, 52, 'key of knowledge', 'Knowledge and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of knowledge and understanding of the law. In Luke, the lawyers hinder those seeking knowledge, while in John, the Pharisees question the understanding of the people regarding the law.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 52, 42, 19, 39, 40, NULL, 'Knowledge and Recognition of Truth', 'This connection highlights the theme of recognition and acceptance of truth. In Luke 11:52, the lawyers hinder those seeking knowledge, while in Luke 19:40, the stones are ready to proclaim the truth if the people remain silent.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 53, 19, 22, 12, 13, NULL, 'Opposition and Hostility Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of opposition faced by the speaker. In both passages, there is a sense of being surrounded and beset by adversaries, whether they are the scribes and Pharisees or the bulls of Bashan.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 53, 23, 9, 12, 12, 'to provoke him to speak', 'Opposition and Divine Anger', 'This connection highlights the theme of provocation and opposition. In Luke, the scribes and Pharisees provoke Jesus, while in Isaiah, Israel faces devouring enemies, indicating ongoing conflict and divine displeasure.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 53, 24, 18, 18, 18, 'urge him vehemently', 'Opposition to Prophetic Voices', 'Both passages emphasize the vehement opposition faced by prophets. In Luke, the scribes and Pharisees provoke Jesus, while in Jeremiah, the people devise plans against him. This connection highlights the consistent theme of resistance to prophetic messages.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 11, 53, 24, 20, 10, 10, 'urge him vehemently', 'Opposition and Defamation', 'This connection highlights the theme of opposition faced by both Jesus and Jeremiah. Both passages depict individuals who are being provoked and watched for their downfall, emphasizing a shared experience of defamation and hostility.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
